<subSubSection id="D1AB14F0DE61FFF3FFC0FBB4B97DFBF8" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="990E477BDE61FFF3FFC0FBB4B97DFBF8" blockId="19.[113,1089,1058,1369]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FFC0FBB4BD9FFB98" bold="true" box="[113,224,1058,1081]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="460AF9D9DE61FFF3FEA6FBB4BC0BFB98" box="[279,372,1058,1081]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">holotype</typeStatus>
is partly dark brown; it is possible that this is not its natural colouration, and it was possibly caused by some treatment of the specimen after collecting.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1AB14F0DE61FFF3FFC0FBF4BE65FB58" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="990E477BDE61FFF3FFC0FBF4BE65FB58" blockId="19.[113,1089,1058,1369]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FFC0FBF4BC12FBD8" bold="true" box="[113,365,1122,1145]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="5EB13CF8DE61FFF3FD68FBF4BE3CFBD8" authorityName="Kaszab" authorityYear="1959" box="[729,835,1122,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonitoschema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranica">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FD68FBF4BE3CFBD8" box="[729,835,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Z. iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above) and differs from it only in its more parallel pronotum; it is distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName id="5EB13CF8DE61FFF3FC1AFB14B93EFB38" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1909" box="[939,1089,1154,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonitoschema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FC1AFB14B93EFB38" box="[939,1089,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Zonitoschema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in the Saharo-Sindian Region by the characters listed in the key. For comparison of this and other species with unicolour elytra, partially red femur and antennomere I yellow, see also above the remarks on 
<taxonomicName id="5EB13CF8DE61FFF3FE06FB74BF5FFB58" authorityName="Kaszab" authorityYear="1959" box="[439,544,1250,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonitoschema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iranica">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FE06FB74BF5FFB58" box="[439,544,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Z. iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5EB13CF8DE61FFF3FDE5FB74BFBFFB58" authority="Batelka &amp; Bologna, 2014" authorityName="Batelka &amp; Bologna" authorityYear="2014" box="[596,704,1250,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonitoschema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FDE5FB74BFBFFB58" box="[596,704,1250,1273]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Z. kaszabi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B0F62612DE61FFF3FD76FB74BE65FB58" box="[711,794,1250,1273]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D1AB14F0DE61FFF3FFC0FA94BC21FAF8" pageId="19" pageNumber="260" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="990E477BDE61FFF3FFC0FA94BC21FAF8" blockId="19.[113,1089,1058,1369]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis id="ABC59B69DE61FFF3FFC0FA94BC7BFAB8" bold="true" box="[113,260,1282,1305]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Distribution.</emphasis>
Described only from the 
<typeStatus id="460AF9D9DE61FFF3FDACFA94BF05FAB8" box="[541,634,1282,1305]" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">holotype</typeStatus>
from western Tassili Mts. in 
<collectingCountry id="E1A607EBDE61FFF3FC0AFA94B971FAB8" box="[955,1038,1282,1305]" name="Algeria" pageId="19" pageNumber="260">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, and recorded here from the 
